 Elevation Financial Group Expands Into Alabama With The Acquisition Of Two Multifamily Properties 
         










    










 






 











 









Elevation Financial Group Expands Into Alabama With The Acquisition Of Two Multifamily Properties

		  Portfolio purchase encompasses a total of 378 units located in the state's capital.
		

Oct 08, 2015, 13:11 ET
		  		  					
						 from   Elevation Financial Group, LLC 











 
















































 

 















































 

 

 
 
 
 







Elevation Financial Group, LLC    
 Facebook
 Twitter
 Pinterest

































 




 




Elevation Financial Group, LLC
 


 

 




 





 


WINTER PARK, Fla., Oct. 8, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Elevation Financial Group, LLC announces the acquisition of two multifamily properties, located in Montgomery, Alabama, for a purchase price of $6.8 million. The portfolio purchase includes Olympia Heights Townhome Apartments, a 202-unit apartment community consisting of 1, 2 and 3-bedroom two-story townhome-style residences and Cyprus Court Apartments, a 176-unit apartment community also consisting of 1, 2 and 3-bedroom two-story garden-style units. Aligning with Elevation's branding strategy, Cyprus Court Apartments will be renamed Serenity Apartments® at the Park and Olympia Heights will be renamed Serenity Townhomes at Montgomery. 
The continued deployment of investor capital from its subsidiary, Elevation Real Property Fund V, LLC, supports Elevation's expansion and presence in the Southeastern region. Both properties are located in the reviving Southeast sector of the Montgomery Loop, an area that has garnered significant attention from city government and local businesses for redevelopment and community investment. 
"This portfolio acquisition represents a wonderful value-add opportunity for our fifth fund and establishes a significant presence and base of operations in Alabama.  We look forward to dramatically revitalizing the physical assets while providing a higher level of quality and service to the residents," said Chris King, CEO of Elevation Financial Group.
Supporting its mission to provide clean, safe and affordable housing, Elevation will undertake extensive renovations to the common areas, amenities and units of both communities. Serenity Townhomes at Montgomery will undergo a comprehensive revitalization to the apartment exteriors, clubhouse pool, and grounds as well as significant interior renovations and upgrades to the units. At Serenity Apartments at the Park, Elevation has recognized the lack of amenities for families and children and in addition to planned renovations to the unit interiors and exteriors will build a park complete with a playground, soccer field and running track. 
The properties will be professionally managed by Elevation Property Management, LLC, an affiliate of Elevation Financial Group with a management portfolio in excess of 2,500 units covering five Southern states.
About Elevation
Elevation Financial Group, a real estate private equity company, leads an award-winning group of companies whose focus and mission is to acquire, revitalize and operate affordable apartment communities for independent seniors and families. As a private equity company, Elevation raises capital through private placements to accredited investors and maintains a commitment to low or no loads on capital raised. Through a consortium of companies specializing in real estate investment, property management and property renovation, Elevation aspires to deliver superior financial returns to its shareholders while making a positive and distinctive impact on the communities we serve.
For further information visit: www.ElevationFinancialGroup.com 
Contact Information:
Angela HowellDirector, Marketing and CommunicationsElevation Financial Group407-215-1350ahowell@elevationfinancialgroup.com
 
Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151008/275304LOGO 
 SOURCE  Elevation Financial Group, LLC  

